For Macos-
> Issue the following from the terminal to tap the official MongoDB Homebrew Tap
brew tap mongodb/brew

> to install MongoDB Community Edition
brew install mongodb-community@4.2

>To run MongoDB (i.e. the mongod process) as a macOS service,
brew services start mongodb-community@4.2

>To stop a mongod running as a macOS service
brew services stop mongodb-community@4.2

> To run MongoDB (i.e. the mongod process) manually as a background process,
>mongod --config /usr/local/etc/mongod.conf --fork

> To verify that MongoDB is running, search for mongod in your running processes:
ps aux | grep -v grep | grep mongod

> To begin using MongoDB, connect a mongo shell to the running instance. From a new terminal, issue the following:

mongo

> TO store some data in collection-
db.eaas.insertMany([{
